\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b sprunerana} (Hampe) Hayek,{\i  Prodr. Fl. Penins. Balcan.}{\b  2}: 545 (1930): Stems 15-50 cm, 1- to 5-flowered, not filiform and flexuous. Middle cauline leaves usually lanceolate, sessile. Corolla 25-30 mm. Calyx-teeth 3-6 times as long as ovary. 2n = 20.{\i  Scrub, mainly lowland. Throughout the range of the species, except Kriti.}
