\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. C. hemschinica} C. Koch,{\i  Linnaea }{\b 23}: 644 (1851). Biennial or perennial. Stems 30-50 cm, erect, angular. Basal and lower cauline leaves oblong-ovate, petiolate; middle cauline oblong-lanceolate, sessile; uppermost acute, crenulate. Flowers in a compact terminal corymbose inflorescence. Calyx-teeth erect 1/4-1/3 as long as the blue corolla. Capsule obconical.{\i  Mountain woods and meadows. • Balkan peninsula.} Bu Ju.
