\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 18. C. stevenii} Bieb.,{\i  Fl. Taur.-Cauc.}{\b  3}: 138 (1819). Perennial. Rhizome procumbent, more or less stoloniferous. Stem 20-50 cm, erect, simple or with few branches, usually 1(to 4)-flowered. Basal leaves oblong-spathulate, acute or obtuse, petiolate; cauline oblong-lanceolate, petiolate, the upper linear-lanceolate, almost sessile. Flowers in a lax inflorescence. Calyx-teeth linear-lanceolate, as long as or longer than ovary. Corolla c. 25 mm, infundibuliform, twice as long as calyx-teeth.{\i  S. part of U.S.S.R.} Rs (C, W, E).
